Effect of HOOC-TEMPO or TEMPO on the Selective Aerobic Oxidation of Methyl Phenyl Sulfide Powered by 660 nm Red Light over PCN-222<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="t1fn1"></xref> Entry TEMPO Conv. (%) Sel. (%) 1 -- 53 98 2 TEMPO 62 98 3 HOOC-TEMPO 85 98

Reaction conditions: PCN-222 (5 mg), CH3OH (1 mL), HOOC-TEMPO (9 μmol), sulfide (0.3 mmol), red LEDs (660 ± 8 nm), air (1 atm), 15 min.

Determined using a gas chromatograph–flame ionization detector (GC–FID) using bromobenzene as the internal standard, conversion of methyl phenyl sulfide, selectivity of methyl phenyl sulfoxide.

Table 1. Effect of HOOC-TEMPO or TEMPO on the Selective Aerobic Oxidation of Methyl Phenyl Sulfide Powered by 660 nm Red Light over PCN-222[^a]

| Entry | TEMPO     | Conv. (%)[^b] | Sel. (%)[^b] |
|-------|-----------|--------------|--------------|
| 1     | --        | 53           | 98           |
| 2     | TEMPO     | 62           | 98           |
| 3     | HOOC-TEMPO| 85           | 98           |

[^a]: Reaction conditions: PCN-222 (5 mg), CH3OH (1 mL), HOOC-TEMPO (9 μmol), sulfide (0.3 mmol), red LEDs (660 ± 8 nm), air (1 atm), 15 min.
[^b]: Determined using a gas chromatograph–flame ionization detector (GC–FID) using bromobenzene as the internal standard, conversion of methyl phenyl sulfide, selectivity of methyl phenyl sulfoxide.
